and governments may actually afford new venues for commodity development and exchange. Presenting prominent case studies of communication law and policy, corporate hacks, and key players in the global cybersecurity market, the book proposes a political economic model of new markets for software vulnerabilities and exploits, and clearly illustrates the social functions of hacking.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aHackers. 0aHackingxPolitical aspects. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Communication Studies.2bisacsh1 aMcCourt, Tom, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066763940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520971653?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520971653423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520971653/original  a978-3-11-066763-9  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-SEWb2020